1. Which variables in the dataset appear to significantly impact sales? Describe the relationships between these variables and sales.

Based on the dataset, stock availability appear to significantly impact sales. Furthermore, the model displays the relationship between sales and stock availability.

3. How would you characterize the modelâs quality?

I would characterize this model as pretty clean for liner regression. There is a relationship between sales and the number of customers. As the number of customers increase, the number of sales increasingly correspond.


4. What are the general insights that this model provides (i.e., what are the practical
implications of the model, how could it be used, etc.)?

Some general insights to be had from this model are understanding what businesses of all sizes need to spend their efforts on. There is a scalable visual from smaller businesses to bigger businesses. Therefore, many other factors like the average price, advertising budget , discount rate, economic condition, and stock availability. Practical uses of this model can be compared against corresponding relationships to determine effectiveness.

eg. This model can be compared against stock availability. It displays that sales grows the most for bigger businesses when they have stock options.
